feed.title: New Mexico (USA)Residential energy efficiency testbed
feed.description:
Single Family residence, frame construction with stucco exterior (simulated "adobe" indigenous regional construction method). High efficiency cooling system, (OASYS, patented by the University of California, Davis CA, Davis Energy Group, in use since May 2008) 2 stage evaporative, custom media, program control.
       Powered negative pressure system for enhanced cooling air circulation and moderate temperature heat removal. Hot water recirculation system; water pressure regulator; low flow toilets; carbon filtered/solid state cooled drinking water system; programmed power-line signalling system/lighting control with radio interface; broadband telephone and data.
       Added internet-based hvac control with wifi interface (12/12/2011). 
        Completed installation of two high efficiency (19-20 SEER) mini-split heat pumps to allow better utilization of areas with selective closures.
